<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920211-0050</DOCNO><DOCID>920211-0050.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Manville Corp.:   Fiberglass Unit Is Renamed   Schuller International Inc.</HL><DATE>02/11/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4</SO><CO>   MVL</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>BUILDING MATERIALS, CONCRETE, GLASS, PAINT (BLD)</IN><RE>COLORADO (CO)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Manville Corp., Denver, said it is changing the name ofone of its two units, partly to discourage investors fromassociating the unit's business with Manville'sasbestos-injury legacy.   The company said Manville Sales Corp. was renamed SchullerInternational Inc., reflecting the name of the Germanfiberglass business, Glaswerk Schuller, which was acquired in1970. The division makes fiberglass and filtration productsand roofing systems.</LP><TEXT>   In June 1991, Manville changed the name of its paperboardunit to Riverwood International Corp., after Manvillereorganized as a holding company. Manville may also changeits corporate name, but that wouldn't happen for a couple ofyears, a spokesman said.   Richard A. Kashnow, president of Schuller, said, &quot;We aremaking the change now to create a strong identity for thissubsidiary and to support our parent company's efforts tohave its securities fairly valued.&quot;</TEXT></DOC>